      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're on the right track by thinking about seed management. One way to structure this is to use a combination of a random number generator and a timestamp-based seed. This will allow you to generate a new seed for each frame, but also keep track of the previous seeds used.\n\nYou can use the `hashlib` library to generate a unique seed based on the current timestamp. This will ensure that you get a different seed every frame, but also allow you to easily roll back to a previous seed.\n\nHere's an example of how you can implement this:\n```python\nimport hashlib\nimport time\n\nclass SeedManager:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.seeds = []\n\n    def get_seed(self):\n        timestamp = int(time.time() * 1000)\n        seed = int(hashlib.sha256(str(timestamp).encode()).hexdigest(), 16)\n        self.seeds.append(seed)\n        return seed\n\n    def rollback(self, seed):\n        if seed in self.seeds:\n            self.seeds.remove(seed)\n            return True\n        return False\n```\nThis `SeedManager` class keeps track of the seeds used in a list, and allows you to generate a new seed and roll back to a previous one. You",
